At Vanithe Sarees, we are thrilled to embark on a new journey, bringing you an exquisite collection of handpicked sarees that celebrate the rich heritage of Indian craftsmanship. Whether you are looking for an elegant silk saree for a grand occasion or a breezy cotton drape for everyday wear, we are here to redefine your wardrobe with timeless elegance. Why Were Back? Fashion evolves, but traditions remain. After a brief pause, we are back stronger, more passionate, and dedicated to curating the finest sarees that blend tradition with contemporary aesthetics. Our mission is to offer sarees that make you feel confident, beautiful, and connected to your roots. Whats New? Curated Collections: From handloom silk to trendy organza, weve got something for every saree lover. Exclusive Designs: Unique weaves, intricate embroidery, and timeless patterns crafted to perfection. Sustainable & Handcrafted: Supporting artisans and promoting eco-friendly fabrics. Shop with Ease: A seamless online shopping experience with doorstep delivery. Style & Grace for Every Occasion Whether its a festive celebration, a wedding, or a casual brunch, our sarees cater to every mood and occasion. Stay tuned for styling tips, fashion inspiration, and exclusive offers designed just for you. Join Us on This Journey Your love and support mean the world to us! Follow Vanithe Sarees on social media and be a part of our growing community of saree enthusiasts. Lets celebrate the beauty of drapes together! Follow us on Instagram & Facebook for the latest collections and styling tips. Shop online and bring home the elegance of Vanithe Sarees. We cant wait to drape you in elegance again! Subject: Were updating our Terms and Community Standards
Body: Facebook The updated Terms will go into effect on January 1, 2025 and weve made our standards easier to find. Were updating our Terms and Community Standards Hi pineapplebhai, Were updating our Terms and Community Standards. The updated Terms will go into effect on January 1, 2025 and we have made our standards easier to find. What you should know Community Standards Our Community Standards describe what is and isnt allowed on our services. Weve brought the standards that apply across Facebook, Instagram, Messenger and Threads together in one place, making them easier for you to find. Terms of Service Our Terms explain what you can expect from us as you use our services, and what we expect from you as a user of our services. Weve made our Terms easier to understand by providing more information about certain existing policies and practices. This includes things like clarifying that people or businesses may still be subject to our Terms when they are logged out or if they access our products without an account. Weve also added links to our Terms for Avatars and AI, which apply if theyre available in your region. What this means for you Our Terms have been updated to reflect these changes, and go into effect on January 1, 2025. By continuing to use our products or the services you receive after that date, you agree to the updated Terms. Learn more about your options if you do not want to agree to the updated Terms. Thank you for using our services, Meta Platforms This message was sent to udgirkarambarishgmail.com at your request. This marks the end of an incredible internship at ConcCoder Services I wanted to take a moment to express my deepest gratitude to my manager and the entire team for such an enriching experience. Your guidance and mentorship have been invaluable. I've learned more than I could have imagined, not just about technology, but also about teamwork, dedication, and pushing beyond limits. Product Innovation: Working on AI and Full Stack Products has been a journey of innovation and growth. I've had the chance to contribute to the Project and witness firsthand how a collaborative team can turn ideas into reality. Learning Curve: The learning curve was steep, but every challenge was an opportunity. I've gained insights that will undoubtedly shape my future endeavors. Exciting Times Ahead: As this chapter closes, I'm thrilled about what the future holds. I'm leaving with a backpack full of skills, memories, and a heart full of gratitude. Thank you, Team ConcCoder, for an unforgettable internship experience. Here's to the next adventure! Subject: Atul Anand shared a post in Machine
Body: Atul Anand shared a post in Machine Learning Community (Moderated): Hi Everyone, I have compiled a few data science interview questions, do let me know important questions in comments so that I can add more. Follow Atul Anand for more!!!!!! machinelearning datascience interviewquestions Comment: Vijay Patil shared a post in Machine Learning Community (Moderated): : Word clouds can provide a quick visual summary of the most prominent words in a text, making it easy to identify key themes, topics, or keywords. : : also known as opinion mining, is the process of determining the sentiment or emotional tone in a piece of text, such as positive, negative, or neutral. ' sentiment analysis tool assigns two sentiment-related properties to the TextBlob object: Polarity: This is a numerical value ranging from -1 (most negative) to 1 (most positive). A polarity of 0 represents a neutral sentiment. Positive values indicate positive sentiment, and negative values indicate negative sentiment. (Affective Norms for English Words) is a pre-built sentiment analysis tool that assigns precomputed sentiment scores to words in the English language. Each word is assigned a numeric score that represents its sentiment polarity, with positive scores indicating a positive sentiment and negative scores indicating a negative sentiment. AFINN is a simple and lightweight resource that can be used for basic sentiment analysis in NLP tasks. : ml mlengineer datascience data dataanalysis dataanalytics dataanalyst data dataanalystjobs datacollection datacareers datacareers dataanalyticsjobs dataanalysisskills nlp deeplearning nlppractitioner textanalysis textanalytics aicommunity artificialintelligence Comment: Farhad Pourkamali Anaraki shared a post in Machine Learning Community (Moderated): Brief tutorial on the use of "conformal prediction" for quantifying uncertainties in the predictions of arbitrary machine learning algorithms. Comment: Google for Developers shared a post: Attention developers: In honor of Firebase Demo Day this Wednesday, November 8th, we have a challenge to test your skills. "Demo Day Live" our imaginary app grapples with a very real problem delayed feedback during live presentations. Harness Firebase's suite of tools to find a speedy resolution. While you ponder the perfect Firebase feature to implement, be sure not to miss the upcoming revelations at Firebase Demo Day on November 8th. Think youve got it? Let us know in the comments! Here, we have explored the role of a variant histone H3 in biofilm formation in an opportunistic fungal pathogen, Candida albicans. A thread... Write if you'd like to develop an experimental/bioinformatics project for a DBT-RA or similar fellowship. There's no other way students will understand the expectations and struggles of an academic system. PhDs and postdocs can have new insights that can improve/sustain your lab. Congratulations on being one of TIME100's Most InfluentialPeople in AI See post: Hotel chains across the country are ramping up recruitment, with new room additions slated to reach more than 14,000 this year, Aneesh Phadnis reports for businessline. Indian Hotels Company Limited, which runs the Taj Group of Hotels, is planning to open 20 properties in FY24 and hire 2,500 direct employees. It has also started a leadership accelerator programme for professionals with MBA degrees, the report says. The Accor Group, which operates brands like Novotel and ibis, is looking to hire 800 employees in 2023, and is offering internal mobility and training programmes to retain staff. Lemon Tree Hotels will also appoint 3,000 people as the companys room count increases from 8,500 to 10,500, says Chairman and MD Patanjali Keswani. Driven by the post-pandemic recovery in the industry, more stalled projects are now getting completed, says Mandeep Singh Lamba, MRICS, President (South Asia) of HVS Anarock. The consulting firm adds that 44% of new room additions will be in Tier 3 locations like Dehradun, Shillong, and Haridwar, among others. Around 10 lakh people are needed in the restaurant industry in the next three quarters, Anumeha Chaturvedi reports for The Economic Times, citing industry executives. Hiring growth is expected to increase by 10-15% during the upcoming festive season, according to Suchita Dutta, Executive Director of the Indian Staffing Federation. There is a shortage of talent at the junior levels across the sector, but the same isnt true at the mid to senior levels, says Nikhil Sharma, Market Managing Director-Eurasia at Wyndham Hotels & Resorts. Body: Your Highlights Praggnanandhaa - rpragchess Read more at Twitter ---------- NASA - NASA Welcome Crew7, to the International SpaceStation. Commander AstroJaws and her crewmates are beginning a mission of about six months living and working on our orbiting lab. Read more at Twitter ---------- Narendra Modi - narendramodi Incredible teamwork at the World Athletics Championships! Subject: NVIDIA shared a post: We're back in
Body: NVIDIA shared a post: We're back in person at the San Jose Convention Center, and online for GTC24. Save the date for GTCthe future-shaping global experience that brings together thousands of innovators, researchers, creators, thought leaders, and decision-makers. It's all happening March 18-21, 2024. See post: Coding Ninjas shared a post: 21DayChallenge: Ninja Slayground (Coding Ninja) Level 2 of the Coding Ninja Slayground Conquered! I'm humbled to showcase the certificate I've earned for completing 7 days of the challenge. The celebration doesn't stop there! As an additional reward, I've received the Ultimate Resume Toolkit and 20% off on any Slay product. Coding Ninjas SLAY Coffee CodingNinjas NinjaSlayground 21daychallenge See post: Intel Corporation shared a post: "You cant understand the world today without putting semiconductors at the center." Recently, Pat Gelsinger and "Chip War" author, Chris Miller sat down at Intel Vision 2023 to talk through the ubiquity of semiconductors and how they shape the balance of power today. Join as they explore some insights in this full interview, See post: AMD shared a post: Today, AMD released our 2022-23 Corporate Responsibility Report, detailing progress toward goals spanning digital impact; environmental sustainability; supply chain responsibility; and diversity, belonging and inclusion. This is our first report to incorporate environmental and social data from recent acquisitions. corporateresponsibility sustainability supplychain DBI environment community AMD TogetherWeAdvance See post: See post: Demand for AI talent from non-tech sectors like healthcare, retail, telecom, and Indian conglomerates is almost 50% higher than last year, according to Michael Page. Companies, including tech firms, are hiring external AI specialists and skilling their workforce on AI. The AI roles in demand? Machine learning engineers, AI security specialists, AI infrastructure managers, AI writers, drone experts, and AI project managers, adds the report. L&T is utilising AI, machine learning, drone, analytics and robotics for pre-cast automation, welding, geospatial mapping, and digital manufacturing. The firm is looking for engineers in the core EPC and construction domains and those with exposure to new technologies, and is hiring for niche roles like AI architects, data scientists, AI infrastructure managers, and AI security specialists, said C Jayakumar, Executive Vice President and Head-Corporate HR. Mondelez India is working on building AI capabilities and workforce, and digital marketing and data science roles are in focus at the company. The company is keen to test and learn AI whether it's for sales or campaigns, said Nagina Singh, People Lead. How will this trend evolve? According to Randstad data, hiring intent for AI-centric roles in non-tech firms has increased 25-30% this year over last. The company expects this trend to pick up as more firms adopt automation and digitisation, said Yeshab Giri, Chief Commercial Officer, Staffing and Randstad Technologies. Indian enterprises increased their AI adoption, with industrial products and manufacturing witnessing the highest adoption rates post-pandemic, reports The Economic Times, citing a PwC survey. While sectors like technology, media, telecom, and healthcare and pharmaceutical have seen progress in AI adoption, the retail and consumer market saw a decline due to a gap in identifying potential use cases, according to the report. Source: The Economic Times: : Isha Chitnis : Getty Images ArtificialIntelligence MachineLearning HiringIndia TechandInnovation See post: Qualcomm shared a post: Looking to enhance your knowledge of 5G Release 16? Body: You have 1 new invitation View invitations: Congratulate Purva Chalindrawar for starting a new position as Management Trainee at Younity.in Say congrats Purva Chalindrawar shared a post: I am delighted to share that I have successfully completed an enriching internship at Younity.in, a remarkable journey that has been both educational and rewarding. During this period, I had the privilege of working under the mentorship of Amandeep Kaur Mam , whose guidance and expertise have been invaluable in shaping my professional growth. The internship provided me with a multifaceted learning experience, encompassing essential skills such as marketing, interpersonal communication, and relationship building. I am proud to mention that I contributed significantly to the organization's success by generating a commendable revenue of over 10K, showcasing my dedication and commitment to achieving tangible results. This internship, which was stipend-based, not only allowed me to expand my horizons but also led to my promotion to the role of Management Trainee due to my exceptional performance. I am now serving as a team leader, where I can leverage my skills and experiences to drive further growth and success for the team and the organization. I am elated to have been recognized for my efforts with both a completion certificate and an excellence certificate, a testament to the quality of work I have delivered throughout this journey. These certificates serve as a testament to my dedication, competence, and accomplishments during this internship and I look forward to utilizing these experiences to contribute positively to future endeavors. leadership internship Younity.in Comment: Coding Ninjas shared a post: Tag your friends and ask them for a coffee!
